# 3. Miscellaneous Functions (M Codes)

Miscellaneous functions control machine behavior such as spindle movement, coolant activation, and program flow.

## 3.1 Program Control

| Code | Description                                               |
| ---- | --------------------------------------------------------- |
| M00  | Programmed stop. Machine pauses until manually resumed.   |
| M01  | Optional stop. Executes only if optional stop is enabled. |
| M17  | End of subprogram.                                        |
| M30  | End of program and full reset.                            |

---

## 3.2 Spindle Control

| Code | Description                             |
| ---- | --------------------------------------- |
| M03  | Spindle ON – clockwise rotation.        |
| M04  | Spindle ON – counterclockwise rotation. |
| M05  | Spindle OFF. Cancels M03 and M04.       |

---

## 3.3 Tool and Coolant Control

| Code | Description                          |
| ---- | ------------------------------------ |
| M06  | Tool change (must follow T command). |
| M08  | Coolant ON.                          |
| M09  | Coolant OFF.                         |

