# 7. Linear Interpolation and Positioning

---

# 7.1 Rapid Positioning – G00

```
G00 X__ Y__ Z__
```

* Rapid traverse movement
* No cutting operation
* Used for positioning
* Modal command

---

# 7.2 Linear Cutting Movement – G01

```
G01 X__ Y__ Z__ F__
```

* Linear interpolation
* Controlled feed rate
* Used during material removal
* Modal command

---

# 8. Engineering Notes

* Modal commands reduce redundancy in programs.
* Proper use of work offsets improves setup efficiency.
* Exact stop mode improves sharp geometry but increases cycle time.
* Continuous mode improves surface finish and machining speed.
* Clean block structure improves readability and safety.

